  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison says that today is the 40th anniversary of the &quot;Declaration of Sentiments,&quot; forming the American Anti-Slavery Society. Garrison comments on &quot;what a change has been wrought in the condition and destiny of the colored population of the United States.&quot; He regrets that reform &quot;in any of its multitudinous phases&quot; is never talked about at the coffee parties attended by Fanny Garrison Villard in Germany. Garrison says: &quot;It is most gratifying to hear of the improved state of Harry&apos;s health.&quot;</subfield>
